  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime of $25,000 and has already undertaken partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a long prison sentence is disproportionate for this specific sum and criminal history. The outburst from the spectator is irrelevant to the legal sentencing guidelines. Considering the mitigation of the first-time offense and partial repayment, a sentence of 6 months is sufficient to serve as a deterrent and punishment without being overly punitive.",
